text: The osculating orbit of an astronomical object is the gravitational Kepler orbit. This is the normal orbit it would have around a body, supposing it were not perturbed (disturbed) by a third body.Moulton, Forest R. 1970. [1902] Introduction to Celestial Mechanics (2nd revised ed).
